        "body": "I don't think this is worth adding. As you say, the UTF-8 spec already discourages using a BOM when feasible, and I don't see any reason why it being a Java source file introduces further complexity that merits calling this out in the style guide. I'm not certain I've ever even seen a UTF-8 file with a BOM...",
